<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-27T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-27T06:00:00-05:00" n="21" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d21">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">883.0513/180: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Fish</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-27T13:00:00+02:00">November 27, 1936—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 27—11:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>67. Legation’s telegram No. 65. I would appreciate some indication from
                            the Department as to when reply may be forthcoming as it is desirable,
                            now that I am again in Egypt, for me to be able to give the Egyptian
                            authorities some assurances on the subject.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>